##
# madwifi - Wireless LAN chipsets from Atheors.
#

= Document =
 * A wireless card compatibility matrix
   http://madwifi.org/wiki/Compatibility
 * http://madwifi.org/wiki/DevDocs/AthDebug

= Kernel Requirements =
 * No module versioning support (CONFIG_MODVERSIONS)
 * Wireless Extensions support in kernel (CONFIG_NET_RADIO)
 * Sysctl support in kernel (CONFIG_SYSCTL)
 * Crypto API support in kernel (CONFIG_CRYPTO)
 * HMAC support (CONFIG_CRYPTO_HMAC)
 * AES support (for WPA networks) (CONFIG_CRYPTO_AES)

= madwifi tools =
 * 80211stats -  simple tool to display collected madwifi 802.11 statistics
 * athstats - simple tool to inspect and monitor network traffic statistics
 * athkey - manage encryption type and keys of madwifi devices
 * athchans - define channel range of madwifi devices
 * athctrl - sets the maximum distance between communicating stations
 * athdebug - control the debug output from the madwifi device subsystem
 * 80211debug - control the debug output from the madwifi 802.11 stack
 * wlanconfig - Create, destroy and manipulate madwifi VAPs

= wireless tools =
 * iwevent - Display Wireless Events generated by drivers and setting changes
 * iwgetid -  Report ESSID, NWID or AP/Cell Address of wireless network
 * iwconfig - configure a wireless network interface
   * essid
   * mode: Ad-Hoc, Managed, Master, Repeater, Secondary, Monitor, Auto
   * channel: 1-11, auto, off
   * key
 * iwspy - Get wireless statistics from specific nodes
 * iwlist - Get more detailed wireless information from a wireless interface
 * iwpriv - configure optionals (private) parameters of a wireless network
   interface 
 * ifrename - rename network interfaces based on various static criteria

